@startuml

title Phase 5: User Data Viewing

actor USER
participant WEB
participant Server
participant "PostgreSQL" as DB

note over USER, DB
  This phase is the  **read path** only.
  ESP32 and MQTT Broker are not involved.
  The user accesses a web dashboard to
  view device status, watering history,
  and manage configuration.
end note

activate USER

== 5.1 Device List ==

USER -> WEB ++: Open dashboard\nGET /

WEB -> Server ++: **GET** /api/devices

Server -> DB ++: SELECT\n\
|_ device_id, status,\n\
|_ firmware_version,\n\
|_ last_seen_at\n\
FROM devices\nORDER BY last_seen_at DESC
DB -->> Server --: Result set (N rows)

Server -->> WEB: **HTTP 200**\n\
|_ body = {\n\
|_   "devices": [\n\
|_     {\n\
|_       "device_id": "GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX",\n\
|_       "status": "active",\n\
|_       "firmware_version": "1.0.0",\n\
|_       "last_seen_at": "2026-03-05T14:30:02Z"\n\
|_     }\n\
|_   ]\n\
|_ }
deactivate Server

WEB -->> USER: Device list table\n(device ID, status, firmware, last seen)

== 5.2 Device Detail ==

USER -> WEB: Click on device "GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX"

WEB -> Server ++: **GET** /api/devices/GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX

Server -> DB ++: SELECT * FROM devices\nWHERE device_id = 'GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX'
DB -->> Server --: Device row

Server -> DB ++: SELECT * FROM device_configs\nWHERE device_id = 'GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX'\nAND status = 'applied'\nORDER BY port
DB -->> Server --: Config rows (port 1, port 2)

Server -> DB ++: SELECT * FROM watering_events\nWHERE device_id = 'GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX'\nORDER BY device_timestamp DESC\nLIMIT 10
DB -->> Server --: Recent watering events

Server -->> WEB: **HTTP 200**\n\
|_ body = {\n\
|_   "device_id": "GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX",\n\
|_   "mac_address": "AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF",\n\
|_   "firmware_version": "1.0.0",\n\
|_   "hardware_revision": "rev3",\n\
|_   "status": "active",\n\
|_   "first_seen_at": "...",\n\
|_   "last_seen_at": "...",\n\
|_   "configs": [\n\
|_     {"port": 1, "config_id": "cfg-...",\n\
|_      "status": "applied", ...},\n\
|_     {"port": 2, "config_id": "cfg-...",\n\
|_      "status": "applied", ...}\n\
|_   ],\n\
|_   "recent_watering": [ ... ]\n\
|_ }
deactivate Server

WEB -->> USER: Device detail page:\n\
|_ Status card (device info)\n\
|_ Port 1 config panel\n\
|_ Port 2 config panel\n\
|_ Recent watering timeline

== 5.3 Watering History (per port) ==

USER -> WEB: Select **Port 1** tab\nSet date range: 2026-03-01 to 2026-03-05

WEB -> Server ++: **GET** /api/devices/GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX/watering\n\
|_ ?port=1\n\
|_ &from=2026-03-01T00:00:00Z\n\
|_ &to=2026-03-05T23:59:59Z\n\
|_ &limit=50

Server -> DB ++: SELECT * FROM watering_events\nWHERE device_id = 'GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX'\n\
AND port = 1\n\
AND device_timestamp\n\
  BETWEEN '2026-03-01' AND '2026-03-05'\nORDER BY device_timestamp DESC\nLIMIT 50
DB -->> Server --: Result set

Server -->> WEB: **HTTP 200**\n\
|_ body = {\n\
|_   "device_id": "GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX",\n\
|_   "port": 1,\n\
|_   "from": "2026-03-01T00:00:00Z",\n\
|_   "to": "2026-03-05T23:59:59Z",\n\
|_   "count": 12,\n\
|_   "watering_events": [\n\
|_     {\n\
|_       "event": "watering_stopped",\n\
|_       "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:02:00Z",\n\
|_       "trigger": "schedule",\n\
|_       "actual_duration_s": 120,\n\
|_       "humidity_at_stop_pct": 55.7,\n\
|_       "stop_reason": "duration_complete"\n\
|_     },\n\
|_     ...\n\
|_   ]\n\
|_ }
deactivate Server

WEB -->> USER: Watering history table:\n\
|_ Date/time, trigger type,\n\
|_ duration, humidity before/after,\n\
|_ stop reason

== 5.4 Config Status ==

USER -> WEB: Open config panel for **Port 2**

WEB -> Server ++: **GET** /api/devices/GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX/config\n\
|_ ?port=2

Server -> DB ++: SELECT * FROM device_configs\nWHERE device_id = 'GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX'\nAND port = 2\nORDER BY created_at DESC\nLIMIT 1
DB -->> Server --: Latest config row

Server -->> WEB: **HTTP 200**\n\
|_ body = {\n\
|_   "config_id": "cfg-20260305-002",\n\
|_   "port": 2,\n\
|_   "watering_schedule": [\n\
|_     {"time": "07:00", "duration_s": 90}\n\
|_   ],\n\
|_   "humidity_threshold_pct": 40,\n\
|_   "status": "applied",\n\
|_   "created_at": "2026-03-05T10:00:00Z",\n\
|_   "acked_at": "2026-03-05T10:00:03Z"\n\
|_ }
deactivate Server

WEB -->> USER: Config panel for port 2:\n\
|_ Schedule: 07:00 (90s)\n\
|_ Humidity threshold: 40%\n\
|_ Status: Applied

== 5.5 Update Config (triggers Phase 3) ==

USER -> WEB: Edit port 2 threshold to 45%\nClick **Save**

WEB -> Server ++: **POST** /api/devices/GB-XXXXXXXXXXXX/config\n\
|_ body = {\n\
|_   "port": 2,\n\
|_   "watering_schedule": [\n\
|_     {"time": "07:00", "duration_s": 90}\n\
|_   ],\n\
|_   "humidity_threshold_pct": 45\n\
|_ }

ref over Server
  This triggers the  **Phase 3**
  config protocol flow:
  INSERT → PUBLISH → device ack.
  See **phase3-config-protocol.puml**
end ref

Server -->> WEB: **HTTP 201 Created**\n\
|_ body = {\n\
|_   "config_id": "cfg-20260305-003",\n\
|_   "port": 2,\n\
|_   "status": "pushed"\n\
|_ }
deactivate Server

WEB -->> USER: Config saved.\nStatus: Pushed\n(awaiting device acknowledgment)

deactivate USER

@enduml
